<BlogPost
  title="2018 Husqvarna FX 450 test Oregon vs Arizona"
  description=""
  category="Uncategorized"
  categorySlug="uncategorized"
>
<p>Hi there, I&#8217;ve put 100 hours on the 450 now, in both areas. The soupy singletrack of the northwest, and the dry-bone trails of Arizona. I can say with all confidence, the low end grunt is incredible, no suprise. No matter what the challenge, the 450 is the low end king and will chug, rumble, and pull with authority over loose muddy roots, or super sandy ledges. Let&#8217;s preface this blog with the rear tire control subject; IRC cheater, with tubliss setup at 7 lbs or less, in both types of terrain. In the mud, I have to say, it&#8217;s the 450 is the clear winner. With super hookup, and chug that grabs onto any surface except icy packed soil with finesse. From smooth to lightly beaten down, the bike is a clear advantage over my favorite 300 when hitting the power down low. In the sandy, ball-bearing over concrete trails of Arizona is where the differences are really noticeable. My 300&#8217;s floats over loose baby-headed sandy climbs much easier, as it seems to have a smoother throttle response. The 450 throws, and spews every bit of loose matter in it&#8217;s way when trying to crest an uphill, pulling the rider offline when timing is critical. The beast is loose in this situation, and more throttle control is required to keep the 450 hooked up. I&#8217;ve seen it over and over with riders coming down to AZ wanting the 450 over the 300, and having to adjust their power delivery. Out in the open, moving with speed, the gloves are off, and obviously things change with momentum, where you become a 4-stroke or 2-stroke rider who prefers the chug over the braaap. Cheers Doug<img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2647" src="https://www.oregonmotorcyclerental.com/newsite/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350-300x171.jpeg" alt="" width="300" height="171" srcset="../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350-300x171.jpeg 300w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350-256x146.jpeg 256w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350-50x28.jpeg 50w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350-132x75.jpeg 132w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2016/07/2017-Husqvarna-FX-350.jpeg 750w" sizes="(max-width:767px) 300px, 300px" /></p>
